main event: Several unidentified objects were observed over the Pacific Northwest region on multiple occasions, moving at high speeds and sometimes hovering.
interesting points: The sighting includes both dim and bright objects observed during daylight., The objects exhibited varied courses and maneuvers as they appeared to change altitude rapidly., The radar operator noted the unidentified target traveled faster than any known aircraft., A Coast Guard report suggested that small moving objects with sharp breaking curves were observed along with the unidentified tracks., No photographic evidence was found in the documentation of the sightings.
location: Pacific Northwest, Washington and Oregon States
witness description: Captain S. P. Dale, USAF, reported the radar observations related to the unidentified objects.
